                <p>The z/OS system that you use to provision a 'brand new' z/OS system is known as the provisioning system. Some planning and setup is required to enable the provisioning system to drive the provisioning of a 'brand new' z/OS system. This work involves some host system customization and modification of the provisioning template's properties file.</p>
                <p class='ibm-ind-link'><a class='ibm-forward-link' href='https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/zos/latest?topic=services-provisioning-zos-software-instance'>How to plan for z/OS system provisioning</a></p>"
            },
            {
                subSectionTitle: "Steps",
                subSectionContent: "<p>To prepare a software services template and provision software, perform these steps using the Software Services task of z/OSMF:</p>
                <ol><li>Expand the Cloud Provisioning category in the navigation area, then select Software Services.</li>
                <li>Select the Templates tab.</li>
                <li>In the table, click Add Template, then select either Standard or Composite to specify the type of template that you want to create.If Add Template is not available, it might be because you are not a domain administrator.</li>
                <li>On the page that is displayed, supply values.</li></ol>
                <p>The steps for creating a z/OS system provisioning template are similar to the steps that you follow for creating other types of software services templates.</p>
                <li><a href='https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/zos/latest?topic=pzsi-steps-provisioning-zos-software-instance'>How to create a z/OS provisioning template (see steps 5-7)</a></li>"
